WEBVTT

00:01.333 --> 00:04.125
I'm gonna explode, man.
My insides are gurgling.

00:04.125 --> 00:06.250
Who gurgles at 16
unless they're gonna explode?

00:06.250 --> 00:07.458
You're not
gonna explode.

00:07.458 --> 00:09.000
Really. How do you
know that, huh?

00:09.000 --> 00:09.834
Some guy in Norway

00:10.208 --> 00:11.500
blew up in the middle
of a supermarket last year.

00:11.750 --> 00:14.208
Nervous anticipation doesn't
cause spontaneous combustion.

00:14.208 --> 00:15.500
Who said I was nervous?

00:15.500 --> 00:16.875
Pacey, it's nervous
that you're--

00:16.875 --> 00:18.166
natural that you're
nervous, man.

00:18.166 --> 00:19.708
You see Andie in, what,
less than six hours?

00:19.708 --> 00:22.000
Five hours and 20 minutes,
if the traffic's right.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.333
-[GRUNTS]
-[LAUGHS]

00:23.333 --> 00:25.291
Ok, so I'm a little nervous,
man, but what do you expect?

00:25.625 --> 00:27.375
Is her dad still letting you
pick her up?

00:27.375 --> 00:29.667
Absolutely. This train
cuts at lunch.

00:29.667 --> 00:30.792
You need
some company?

00:31.417 --> 00:33.000
Actually, Joey's
gonna come with me.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.208
Yeah. She wants
to see Andie,

00:34.208 --> 00:36.375
and per our
conversation last week--

00:36.375 --> 00:38.041
Absolutely. Please.
Nobody welcomes

00:38.041 --> 00:40.000
a Potter-Witter détente
more than me.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.291
Glad she has somebody.

00:41.917 --> 00:43.542
It'll only help
as Joey and I

00:43.542 --> 00:45.041
weave our separate ways

00:45.041 --> 00:47.375
through these pathless woods
we call life.

00:47.708 --> 00:50.125
Hey. Speaking of wood,
Dawson...

00:50.875 --> 00:52.792
What ever happened
with a certain bus girl?

00:52.792 --> 00:54.583
[SIGHS]
Don't ask.

00:54.583 --> 00:56.208
She vanished.
Disappeared.

00:56.208 --> 00:58.417
Jonathan Krakauer-ed
Into Thin Air.

00:58.959 --> 01:00.208
You let her get away?

01:00.542 --> 01:03.458
I had a slightly irate
father to answer to, Pacey.

01:03.458 --> 01:05.500
I'm lucky I got away
with my life, you know.

01:05.750 --> 01:07.083
So what's happened since?

01:07.083 --> 01:09.542
With Eve? I haven't
been able to find her.

01:09.542 --> 01:11.542
Did you check down
at the strip joint?

01:11.542 --> 01:13.041
Embarrassingly, yes.

01:13.041 --> 01:14.208
She doesn't even
work there anymore.

01:14.208 --> 01:15.750
Turns out
she was a temp.

01:16.667 --> 01:18.000
Strip joints have temps?

01:18.000 --> 01:20.583
The only information I have
about her is her first name,

01:20.583 --> 01:21.792
and who even knows
if that's for real?

01:21.792 --> 01:23.542
[GROANS]
That is really too bad, Dawson,

01:23.542 --> 01:26.208
because Eve was the ultimate
transitional woman.

01:26.208 --> 01:27.583
How do you figure?

01:27.583 --> 01:30.291
Well, you are coming off
of an emotionally traumatic,

01:30.291 --> 01:31.875
life-altering relationship.

01:31.875 --> 01:33.250
The last thing
that you need to be doing

01:33.250 --> 01:35.083
is get emotionally
involved again. Right?

01:35.083 --> 01:36.917
But being that you are a
young, virile,

01:36.917 --> 01:38.500
increasingly buff teenage male,

01:38.500 --> 01:40.125
you have certain wants
and desires.

01:40.125 --> 01:43.375
Enter Eve-- A gift from the gods
on rebound high,

01:43.375 --> 01:46.000
a curvaceous vixen who
was meant for you to be explored

01:46.000 --> 01:47.792
in only a sexual manner,

01:47.792 --> 01:50.458
a femme fatale whose
entire genetic coding

01:50.458 --> 01:52.041
screams "objectify me."

01:52.041 --> 01:54.083
I'm telling you, Dawson,
if you ever find her again,

01:54.083 --> 01:56.959
do not let her
out of your... sight...

01:58.291 --> 01:59.250
Dawson?

01:59.583 --> 02:01.667
[METAL CLANGS]

02:04.417 --> 02:05.375
Eve.

02:05.375 --> 02:06.667
Morning, Dawson.

02:07.166 --> 02:08.834
Welcome to school.

02:14.125 --> 02:17.250
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

03:02.625 --> 03:03.583
[LIPS SMACK]

03:04.333 --> 03:06.333
Immediate thought--
What are you doing here?

03:06.625 --> 03:08.166
At 11:00, I'm popping
out of a cake

03:08.166 --> 03:10.000
for Mr. Sax in AP History.

03:10.333 --> 03:12.959
Duh. I'm, like,
a student.

03:13.250 --> 03:14.417
You are not.

03:14.417 --> 03:15.834
What's the matter,
Dawson?

03:15.834 --> 03:17.917
Never seen a senior girl
up close before?

03:18.417 --> 03:19.625
I've seen plenty
of senior girls,

03:19.625 --> 03:21.667
but none of them
looked like you.

03:21.667 --> 03:22.917
Plus, you've gotta
be at least--

03:22.917 --> 03:24.000
Watch it.

03:24.417 --> 03:25.500
Older than I am.

03:25.834 --> 03:27.667
Somehow, I thought
you'd be more excited

03:27.667 --> 03:28.875
by my sudden appearance.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.500
I'm... very excited.
It's just that

03:30.500 --> 03:32.708
it's usually followed
by a sudden disappearance.

03:33.542 --> 03:34.542
I mean...

03:34.875 --> 03:36.834
Who are you, Eve?
[LAUGHS]

03:36.834 --> 03:38.959
First, you're this stunning
passenger on my bus,

03:38.959 --> 03:40.708
striking up conversation,
and then...

03:41.166 --> 03:42.250
You're wearing a wig,

03:42.250 --> 03:43.375
serving cocktails
in a strip club.

03:43.375 --> 03:45.375
Now you're a senior
at my high school.

03:45.375 --> 03:47.125
You've got it
all wrong, Dawson.

03:47.542 --> 03:49.083
I'm none of those things.

03:50.542 --> 03:51.959
I'm just a girl...

03:52.500 --> 03:54.625
Standing
in a janitor's closet...

03:55.583 --> 03:57.166
Asking you to kiss her.

04:00.750 --> 04:02.708
[BELL RINGS]

04:03.291 --> 04:05.333
Late for bio. See ya.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.375
Hold on.

04:07.375 --> 04:09.208
[CLATTERING]

04:09.208 --> 04:10.625
Can I at least get
your last name this time?

04:10.625 --> 04:13.000
Hey! It's, uh, Leery,
but you can call me Dad.

04:13.291 --> 04:15.250
Listen, the principal and I
were just talkin' about you.

04:15.250 --> 04:17.750
We are in need
of an honest student opinion.

04:17.750 --> 04:18.375
Ok.

04:18.959 --> 04:20.708
The pep rally's tomorrow,
inarguably a critical event

04:20.708 --> 04:22.208
in setting the tone
for this football season.

04:22.208 --> 04:24.083
And with the Minutemen
having such bad luck

04:24.083 --> 04:25.125
the last few years,

04:25.125 --> 04:26.500
and in light of me
being the new coach...

04:26.500 --> 04:28.333
We thought we would do something
to revolutionize this,

04:28.333 --> 04:30.166
set this pep rally apart
from all the other ones.

04:30.166 --> 04:31.458
-So what do you think?
-Sounds good.

04:31.458 --> 04:32.417
I'm gonna need your help.

04:32.417 --> 04:33.750
I'll see you in my office
at 3:00.

04:33.750 --> 04:34.667
Oh, hold on I--

04:34.667 --> 04:35.917
Very wise of you
to help out, son,

04:35.917 --> 04:37.458
in light of the fact
that you owe me.

04:37.458 --> 04:40.208
[SIGHS]
It is so not my day.

04:41.417 --> 04:43.125
Well, I can't
thank you enough.

04:43.125 --> 04:44.417
After a year
with Jennifer,

04:44.417 --> 04:47.500
having Jack was like
boarding Saint Francis.

04:47.500 --> 04:49.208
[LAUGHS]
When does Andie get in?

04:49.500 --> 04:51.917
Tonight. Pacey wanted
to surprise her

04:51.917 --> 04:53.125
and bring her home early.

04:53.125 --> 04:55.041
She's made a full recovery then?

04:55.542 --> 04:56.750
That's what
the doctors say,

04:56.750 --> 04:58.083
although they like
to remind you that

04:58.333 --> 05:00.917
with mental illness,
you're never out of the woods.

05:00.917 --> 05:03.417
Well, you've given that girl
an excellent chance

05:03.417 --> 05:04.667
by moving your business
this way

05:04.667 --> 05:06.291
so that she can stay
in Capeside.

05:06.792 --> 05:08.458
About that, Dad.
I was wondering.

05:08.458 --> 05:09.625
Maybe we could wait
till the weekend

05:09.625 --> 05:10.959
and move all my stuff back
into the house.

05:10.959 --> 05:13.041
Actually, that's what I've
come to talk to you about.

05:13.750 --> 05:15.625
Why don't I give
you two a moment?

05:17.917 --> 05:19.083
[DOOR OPENS]

05:19.375 --> 05:22.959
I was... thinking
that... perhaps it-- it...

05:22.959 --> 05:25.625
Might be better
for you to stay here a while,

05:25.625 --> 05:27.708
as long as it's all right
with Mrs. Ryan.

05:28.583 --> 05:29.792
You don't want me home?

05:30.125 --> 05:31.917
You have a situation
that works for you.

05:31.917 --> 05:33.583
I don't think it's wise
to disturb that.

05:33.583 --> 05:35.834
You mean you have
a situation that works for you.

05:36.208 --> 05:38.834
The changes that you're going
to make in your life now,

05:39.125 --> 05:41.875
changes you have
every right to make,

05:42.333 --> 05:44.458
would be too difficult
with me around.

05:46.166 --> 05:48.166
Why can't you just admit
that you're afraid?

05:48.166 --> 05:49.625
You can't deal
with having a gay son,

05:49.625 --> 05:51.500
and having me around
would mean doing just that.

05:51.500 --> 05:53.583
Must you assume that
every decision I make

05:53.583 --> 05:55.083
is based upon my lack
of character?

05:55.083 --> 05:57.041
No. Just the ones
that concern me.

05:57.542 --> 05:58.875
Well, since this
is still my home,

05:58.875 --> 06:00.458
I suggest you leave.

06:01.834 --> 06:04.708
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

06:07.500 --> 06:09.291
[DOOR CLOSES]

06:11.750 --> 06:14.291
Andie McPhee is scheduled
to be released tomorrow,

06:14.291 --> 06:15.250
not today.

06:15.250 --> 06:17.208
That's why it's a surprise.

06:17.208 --> 06:18.875
We try to avoid surprises.

06:18.875 --> 06:22.166
The only way she leaves today
is with her own written consent.

06:22.166 --> 06:24.375
Which I will get if you'll just
let me walk

06:24.375 --> 06:25.542
in the door and talk to her.

06:25.542 --> 06:27.834
And that will be
tomorrow morning at 9 a.m.

06:27.834 --> 06:29.583
When visiting hours resume.

06:29.583 --> 06:30.625
Not a minute earlier.

06:30.625 --> 06:32.166
You gotta
be kiddin' me.

06:32.166 --> 06:34.041
Does this look like
a face that kids?

06:34.583 --> 06:37.083
-This is ridiculous.
-JOEY: What happened?

06:37.083 --> 06:39.375
Well, the clinic doesn't allow
visitors after hours.

06:39.375 --> 06:41.542
Subsequently, I can't talk
to Andie, and subsequently,

06:41.542 --> 06:43.375
I can't get her permission
to take her home.

06:44.542 --> 06:45.458
[GRUNTS]

06:46.542 --> 06:47.583
What?

06:48.792 --> 06:49.708
Follow me.

06:50.542 --> 06:51.708
You don't understand.

06:51.708 --> 06:53.542
I have to see a doctor
immediately.

06:53.542 --> 06:55.375
This is a private care facility.

06:55.375 --> 06:56.750
Unless it's a medical
emergency,

06:56.750 --> 06:58.250
we do not take walk-ins.

06:58.250 --> 06:59.500
This is a moral injustice.

06:59.500 --> 07:02.291
-I have psychiatric concerns.
-Well, obviously.

07:03.041 --> 07:05.917
Fine. If that's the way it is,
I guess you'll just have to do.

07:06.333 --> 07:07.417
Excuse me?

07:07.667 --> 07:08.792
Well, somebody's
gotta listen to me.

07:09.083 --> 07:11.250
I've had a tough life, lady,
and I have a lot to talk about.

07:11.583 --> 07:13.000
See, it all started
when I fell in love

07:13.000 --> 07:14.250
with this boy down the creek.

07:14.250 --> 07:16.667
And... that was after
my mother died of cancer,

07:16.667 --> 07:19.417
but before my father went
to prison for the second time.

07:20.667 --> 07:23.917
The boy's name was Dawson,
and he was your typical,

07:23.917 --> 07:25.917
over-analytical,
adorable teenager,

07:25.917 --> 07:27.917
who happened to be
my best friend.

07:27.917 --> 07:29.291
That's propaganda.

07:29.291 --> 07:31.959
In a word, yes, and it's
the only chance we have

07:31.959 --> 07:33.625
of getting people
into those seats.

07:33.959 --> 07:35.917
Now, listen. Dawson,
all I need right now

07:35.917 --> 07:37.542
is somebody to recut
this footage

07:37.875 --> 07:39.792
into some sort of promotional
film for tomorrow.

07:39.792 --> 07:42.125
Now, your father says
you're the man for the job.

07:42.458 --> 07:43.583
Footage of what?

07:43.583 --> 07:44.458
The Minutemen.

07:44.458 --> 07:46.291
Our fearless champions
of the turf.

07:46.291 --> 07:49.291
Ambassadors of sport.
Paragons of athletic prowess.

07:49.291 --> 07:51.083
They're winless
three years running.

07:52.291 --> 07:54.583
Listen, I know
what the reality is.

07:54.583 --> 07:56.125
But the footage wouldn't
emphasize what is,

07:56.125 --> 07:57.583
but what could be.

07:57.583 --> 08:00.333
[CHUCKLING]
The Leni Reifenstahl approach.

08:00.625 --> 08:02.375
You know, the Nazis
did this, too.

08:02.375 --> 08:04.333
[SIGHS]
Dawson...

08:04.875 --> 08:06.083
Throughout history,

08:06.083 --> 08:08.166
film has proven to be
a highly effective medium.

08:08.166 --> 08:10.667
Now, Capra, he used it
to recruit American troops

08:10.667 --> 08:11.792
to fight World War II.

08:12.125 --> 08:15.166
Annie Hall  inspired
countless scores of women

08:15.166 --> 08:17.542
to start to wear men's apparel.
I'm tellin' you--

08:17.542 --> 08:19.542
You know what? I'll do it.
I'll do it.

08:19.542 --> 08:20.917
Can I-- can I go now?

08:23.959 --> 08:25.792
EVE: Slow down,
Buster Brown.

08:26.291 --> 08:27.708
I'm warning you,
this is the last time

08:27.708 --> 08:28.792
I'm gonna chase you.

08:29.333 --> 08:30.834
Ok, I spent a year
chasing a woman.

08:30.834 --> 08:31.959
It's a very bad habit.

08:31.959 --> 08:33.332
I don't plan on getting
into it again.

08:33.332 --> 08:35.542
Oh, you're one
of those, are you?

08:36.000 --> 08:36.750
One of whom?

08:37.166 --> 08:38.542
You know. Those guys
who spend the rest of their life

08:38.542 --> 08:40.667
comparing every relationship
to their first one.

08:41.291 --> 08:43.667
That isn't-- not entirely true.

08:44.333 --> 08:45.917
So you're completely over her?

08:46.667 --> 08:49.000
-Over who?
-Nice try.

08:49.333 --> 08:50.834
The brunette it took you
all of 5 minutes

08:50.834 --> 08:52.250
to bring up when we met
on the bus.

08:52.250 --> 08:54.125
Ok, I motion for a change
of subject.

08:54.125 --> 08:55.291
Motion denied.

08:55.750 --> 08:58.625
Are you or are you not
over your ex-flame?

08:59.959 --> 09:00.959
[SIGHS]

09:02.792 --> 09:05.041
Yes.
I'm over her.

09:05.500 --> 09:07.708
Sorry.
Don't buy it.

09:07.708 --> 09:09.542
[SCOFFS]
Then why did you even ask?

09:09.834 --> 09:11.708
To see if you'd be
honest with me.

09:11.708 --> 09:13.917
You weren't.
I like that.

09:15.083 --> 09:16.291
You like dishonesty.

09:16.750 --> 09:18.708
What else turns you on,
greed and corruption?

09:18.708 --> 09:21.583
Sex. Sex turns me on, Dawson.

09:22.917 --> 09:24.375
It tends to do that to people.

09:25.375 --> 09:27.375
And you would know how?

09:27.375 --> 09:28.875
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

09:29.417 --> 09:31.041
I will choose
to ignore that slight.

09:31.375 --> 09:33.041
Maybe it wasn't a slight.

09:33.417 --> 09:35.166
Maybe it was
an invitation.

09:38.041 --> 09:39.417
What are you
suggesting?

09:39.708 --> 09:41.000
Only the obvious.

09:41.458 --> 09:44.208
A night of scorching-hot,
unbridled,

09:44.625 --> 09:46.834
mind-altering sex.

09:48.375 --> 09:49.458
[LAUGHS]

09:49.875 --> 09:51.250
Just like that?
I mean...

09:51.750 --> 09:54.083
No first date, no months
of getting to know each other?

09:54.083 --> 09:57.000
Those are small town rituals
for small town girls.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.792
Let's face it, Dawson,
we're hot for each other.

09:59.792 --> 10:00.667
[SIGHS]

10:00.667 --> 10:02.417
It'd be a lot of fun.

10:03.083 --> 10:05.583
Who knows... maybe
it'll even help you

10:05.583 --> 10:07.959
get over that...
certain brunette.

10:07.959 --> 10:09.458
[EXHALES NERVOUSLY]

10:11.000 --> 10:11.917
You're on.

10:12.166 --> 10:15.542
Good. Now, I'll take
care of the time and place.

10:16.208 --> 10:18.375
You just take care
of being prepared.

10:19.291 --> 10:20.917
How do I find you
in the meantime?

10:20.917 --> 10:22.625
You don't find me, Dawson.

10:23.083 --> 10:24.417
I find you.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.917
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

10:30.333 --> 10:32.000
It is so  my day.

10:42.917 --> 10:45.583
-[WOMAN CHUCKLING]
-MAN: You'll see.

10:46.041 --> 10:47.125
Ok.

10:47.125 --> 10:48.500
[KNOCKING]

10:49.125 --> 10:51.333
Pacey?!
Oh, my god.

10:51.333 --> 10:53.375
What in the world
are you doing here?

10:53.375 --> 10:54.625
I came to surprise you.

10:54.625 --> 10:56.250
Hooh! Yeah! Ok.
[CHUCKLES]

10:56.250 --> 10:57.917
Oh God, it's good to see you.

10:57.917 --> 10:58.959
Yeah!

10:58.959 --> 10:59.959
Um...

10:59.959 --> 11:00.917
Ahhh...

11:00.917 --> 11:03.041
Oh... uh... Mark,

11:03.041 --> 11:05.125
uh, Pacey, Mark.
Mark, this is...

11:05.125 --> 11:06.959
-Hi, man.
-A big surprise.

11:07.458 --> 11:09.417
Um... I thought
my dad said

11:09.417 --> 11:11.166
that he was gonna
pick me up tomorrow.

11:11.166 --> 11:13.708
Yeah, I know. I...
we thought that--

11:13.708 --> 11:14.917
Well, I thought--

11:14.917 --> 11:16.000
Oh, well.
[CHUCKLES]

11:16.500 --> 11:19.041
Uh, it-- it's dinnertime...
for me.

11:19.708 --> 11:21.125
Well... bye, Mark.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.375
We'll talk soon,
I hope.

11:23.834 --> 11:24.959
ANDIE: We will.

11:31.959 --> 11:32.834
Andie.

11:32.834 --> 11:34.583
-Oh! Joey! Hi!
-Hey.

11:34.583 --> 11:35.917
-You came, too!
-Yeah,

11:35.917 --> 11:37.875
and if we don't leave soon,
they're gonna make me stay.

11:37.875 --> 11:38.708
[CHUCKLES]

11:39.458 --> 11:42.500
Yeah. Uh, guess we should
get you packed up, huh?

11:43.834 --> 11:45.166
Right.
[CHUCKLES]

11:56.834 --> 11:58.834
[WHISTLE BLOWS]
One, two, three, four!

11:58.834 --> 12:00.750
We don't care
if we don't score!

12:00.750 --> 12:02.500
Five, six, seven, eight!

12:02.500 --> 12:04.375
A few points would
be really great.

12:04.375 --> 12:06.041
That's all right.
That's ok.

12:06.041 --> 12:08.208
You're gonna work
for us someday.

12:08.208 --> 12:10.667
Go, Capeside!

12:10.667 --> 12:11.917
-What do you think?
-[LAUGHS]

12:11.917 --> 12:13.166
Jen, this is
for a pep rally.

12:13.166 --> 12:15.041
Don't you think they should be
s-slightly more...

12:15.041 --> 12:16.375
-Peppy?
-No, optimistic.

12:16.375 --> 12:18.125
I know, Jack.
I've tried.

12:18.125 --> 12:19.375
Believe me,
I've tried.

12:19.875 --> 12:22.041
Think I want to be
held responsible for killing off

12:22.041 --> 12:24.417
the last vestiges
of Capeside's school spirit?

12:24.959 --> 12:27.208
But ever since they elected
me leader of their little...

12:27.708 --> 12:28.583
