25:36.166 --> 25:38.083
And now for something
a little different

25:38.083 --> 25:39.542
to end tonight's program--

25:39.875 --> 25:42.792
a closer look
at the Capeside Minutemen.

25:44.208 --> 25:46.375
[WANING CHEERS]

25:49.041 --> 25:50.583
DAWSON'S VOICE:
Valor...

25:50.583 --> 25:51.750
Agility...

25:52.083 --> 25:53.166
Determination...

25:54.208 --> 25:55.041
Strength.

25:55.542 --> 25:58.291
In Capeside, we have one word
that means all those things--

25:59.208 --> 26:01.333
EVE: The time has come,
the walrus said...

26:01.333 --> 26:02.750
[MOVIE AUDIO CONTINUES]

26:03.333 --> 26:04.542
You don't mean now?

26:04.917 --> 26:06.834
I pick the time
and place, remember?

26:07.458 --> 26:08.708
But...
[CHUCKLES]

26:08.708 --> 26:11.250
Here? Right-- right now?
I mean, my video's playing.

26:11.250 --> 26:14.291
Which is, like,
the lamest of lamest excuses.

26:15.083 --> 26:16.625
Good point.
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

26:16.625 --> 26:18.417
Dawson, let's go.

26:18.875 --> 26:20.083
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

26:20.083 --> 26:22.125
They say that girls like you
don't exist.

26:22.417 --> 26:23.834
They lie.

26:27.667 --> 26:28.917
[BAG CRINKLES]

26:28.917 --> 26:30.959
Ok, Andie, what the hell
is goin' on?

26:30.959 --> 26:32.417
Ok, and don't tell me
that it's nothin',

26:32.417 --> 26:33.417
because you've
been actin' strange

26:33.667 --> 26:35.250
from the second I picked you
up from that clinic,

26:35.250 --> 26:36.542
and now I have to
beg you to spend

26:36.542 --> 26:39.083
some free time with me.
So what is happening?

26:39.083 --> 26:40.917
We shouldn't talk
about this here, Pacey.

26:41.542 --> 26:42.667
So I'm right.

26:43.250 --> 26:44.959
Look, this is
not the time. Ok?

26:44.959 --> 26:47.041
Is it me? Ok?
Are you trying to end things?

26:47.041 --> 26:48.166
Is that what
this is about?

26:48.166 --> 26:50.667
No! God, that's
the last thing that I want.

26:51.291 --> 26:52.750
Fine. Then
what is so awful

26:52.750 --> 26:55.417
you've waited so long
to tell me about it, Andie?

26:56.291 --> 26:58.959
A lot happened
to me this summer, Pacey. A lot.

27:00.542 --> 27:01.917
What are you
trying to say?

27:04.291 --> 27:06.291
Ok, if we're gonna
talk about this now,

27:06.291 --> 27:07.500
then you have to promise me

27:07.500 --> 27:09.667
that you will not say
one word until I'm done!

27:09.667 --> 27:10.708
Fine, go on.

27:11.083 --> 27:12.500
No. Promise me, Pacey.

27:12.792 --> 27:15.458
Ok. I promise.
just tell me what's wrong.

27:18.208 --> 27:20.417
When I went to Mayfield
to get better...

27:21.125 --> 27:22.500
I wasn't myself anymore.

27:22.500 --> 27:24.625
I-- I wasn't the same person
who came to Capeside.

27:24.625 --> 27:26.417
I wasn't the girl
you fell in love with.

27:26.834 --> 27:28.417
My first week,
I met Mark.

27:28.792 --> 27:30.250
And he had been
through everything

27:30.250 --> 27:31.959
I had been through
and more.

27:33.125 --> 27:35.625
In and out
of facilities three times...

27:35.625 --> 27:36.750
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

27:36.750 --> 27:39.041
On and off medications
since he was nine.

27:40.834 --> 27:42.291
I didn't write you
about him

27:42.792 --> 27:44.333
because I didn't want you
to get jealous.

27:44.333 --> 27:46.500
We were just friends,
you know.

27:46.500 --> 27:48.458
We'd spend
our free time together,

27:48.458 --> 27:52.000
just talking endlessly,
mostly about our fears.

27:53.125 --> 27:55.500
I was so afraid, Pacey.

27:55.500 --> 27:56.375
[SNIFFLES]

27:56.375 --> 27:58.375
Afraid of everything.
[SOBS]

27:58.875 --> 28:00.458
I was scared that they
were never gonna let me

28:00.458 --> 28:02.291
out of there,
or that whatever

28:02.291 --> 28:04.875
was broken inside me
wouldn't be fixable.

28:06.834 --> 28:08.500
[SNIFFLES]
And Mark...

28:09.792 --> 28:12.166
He understood these things
like nobody else could

28:12.166 --> 28:14.500
because they were
his fears, too.

28:17.417 --> 28:21.250
He even had a girlfriend that
he was anxious to get back to.

28:23.417 --> 28:24.792
You slept with him?

28:26.583 --> 28:28.208
We knew immediately afterwards

28:28.208 --> 28:30.375
that it was wrong
for both of us.

28:31.375 --> 28:32.917
You slept with him, Andie.

28:36.125 --> 28:38.208
[WEEPING]

28:38.208 --> 28:40.458
We decided just
to continue to be friends

28:40.458 --> 28:42.041
and not tell
our significant others,

28:42.041 --> 28:43.625
but then when I saw you...

28:45.208 --> 28:46.041
[SNIFFLING]

28:46.291 --> 28:48.542
Pacey, it was
the biggest mistake of my life.

28:48.542 --> 28:49.959
And all I keep
thinking about right now

28:49.959 --> 28:52.166
is what if you can't forgive me?
I mean...

28:52.625 --> 28:54.917
Pacey, you have to
forgive me. please.

28:54.917 --> 28:56.125
You have to forgive me.

29:00.125 --> 29:01.750
[SLAMS DOOR OPEN]

29:06.500 --> 29:08.792
DAWSON'S VOICE: Then there was
the loss to Harrison High.

29:08.792 --> 29:10.417
But did the 20-point difference

29:10.417 --> 29:12.917
discourage our men
of blue and yellow?

29:12.917 --> 29:14.667
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

29:14.667 --> 29:16.083
There is  an audience
of people

29:16.083 --> 29:18.041
on the other side
of the screen.

29:18.375 --> 29:19.417
Isn't it great?

29:19.417 --> 29:21.041
[FILM NARRATION CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY]

29:21.834 --> 29:23.250
You sure there's not
a janitor's closet

29:23.250 --> 29:24.458
we could just duck into?

29:24.458 --> 29:25.542
Positive.

29:26.166 --> 29:28.375
[FILM REEL ROLLING]

29:34.583 --> 29:35.625
What was that?

29:36.208 --> 29:38.250
-What was what?
-That click.

29:38.250 --> 29:40.542
FILM: But here at Capeside,
we may lose the game...

29:40.542 --> 29:42.583
Nothing, Dawson.
[INHALES DEEPLY]

29:42.583 --> 29:43.542
[CLICK]

29:43.542 --> 29:45.583
FILM: ... has the world
by the balls...

29:45.583 --> 29:48.500
-Wait. That was not nothing.
-Relax. I'm sure it's--

29:48.500 --> 29:50.834
FILM: ... just the right amount
with luck and perseverance.

29:50.834 --> 29:52.417
[SCATTERED APPLAUSE]

29:52.417 --> 29:54.041
-Don't turn around.
-[LAUGHTER]

29:54.041 --> 29:55.792
-[HOWLING]
-Why?

29:55.792 --> 29:57.125
[LAUGHTER AND CLAPPING]

29:57.125 --> 29:59.375
[CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

29:59.375 --> 30:00.792
[WHISTLING]

30:00.792 --> 30:03.166
[CHEERING]

30:06.417 --> 30:07.875
Whoo!

30:12.291 --> 30:14.625
[BAND PLAYS]

30:19.625 --> 30:20.834
Whoo!

31:10.166 --> 31:11.542
You ready?

31:13.000 --> 31:15.667
I think I'm gonna catch
a ride home with my father.

31:17.083 --> 31:19.542
You don't wanna...
hang out?

31:20.500 --> 31:21.333
[SIGHS]

31:22.375 --> 31:24.125
Part of me really,
really wants to.

31:25.542 --> 31:27.208
But just part of you.

31:27.750 --> 31:29.542
Eve, I don't know
anything about you.

31:29.542 --> 31:31.542
I don't know
where you come from.

31:31.542 --> 31:32.500
I don't know
why you're here.

31:32.500 --> 31:34.041
I don't even know
your last name.

31:34.708 --> 31:35.917
All you are to me is sex,

31:35.917 --> 31:37.708
and if I slept with you,
that would be the reason.

31:39.125 --> 31:42.083
We all have a reason for
sleeping with someone, Dawson.

31:42.834 --> 31:46.208
Whether it's their body
or their personality,

31:46.208 --> 31:47.959
their money or
their sense of humor.

31:49.333 --> 31:50.625
What's the difference?

31:51.208 --> 31:52.583
I guess the difference is
the first time

31:52.583 --> 31:53.708
I sleep with someone,

31:53.708 --> 31:55.458
I don't want it to be
for just any reason.

31:58.583 --> 32:00.458
I want it to be
for every reason.

32:05.458 --> 32:06.667
Your eyes.

32:07.500 --> 32:08.583
What about 'em?

32:10.166 --> 32:11.375
That was my reason.

32:12.875 --> 32:14.166
When I first met you,

32:15.125 --> 32:16.750
I looked into your eyes,

32:17.750 --> 32:21.208
and I saw such an old soul.

32:23.417 --> 32:24.750
Thank you, Eve.

32:26.750 --> 32:27.959
Whitman.

32:28.834 --> 32:30.750
Thank you, Eve Whitman.

32:32.917 --> 32:33.750
[SIGHS]

32:34.375 --> 32:35.542
I don't suppose there's
any chance

32:35.542 --> 32:37.041
you'd give me
your phone number.

32:37.750 --> 32:39.583
That one
you'll have to earn.

32:46.333 --> 32:48.625
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

32:50.083 --> 32:51.125
[CAR DRIVING]

32:51.542 --> 32:53.625
JOEY: Well, I don't think
we'll be attending any more

32:53.625 --> 32:55.375
pep rallies anytime some.

32:55.375 --> 32:56.708
PACEY: Probably not.

32:56.708 --> 32:58.000
Thanks for the ride.

32:58.000 --> 32:59.041
No problem.

33:00.000 --> 33:02.125
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

33:03.333 --> 33:06.000
Pacey, you probably
don't wanna hear this right now,

33:06.000 --> 33:07.542
and I'm sure you don't
wanna hear it from me,

33:07.542 --> 33:09.291
but you have
to talk to her.

33:09.291 --> 33:12.417
No. Not right now. I couldn't
even look at her right now.

33:13.875 --> 33:16.291
You have to, Pacey.
You have to hear her out.

33:16.291 --> 33:17.834
Why? What's
the difference, Joey?

33:17.834 --> 33:20.667
Huh?! No matter what she says,
the ending's still the same.

33:20.667 --> 33:22.041
She slept with somebody else!

33:22.041 --> 33:24.333
You think that just because
the two of you were together,

33:24.333 --> 33:25.667
what she did to you
hurts more?

33:26.166 --> 33:29.125
It doesn't.
There's no difference, Pacey.

33:29.125 --> 33:30.500
I mean, look...

33:30.500 --> 33:32.458
she's 16-years-old,
and so are you.

33:32.959 --> 33:34.792
We talk like we know
what's going on, but we don't.

33:34.792 --> 33:36.250
We don't have any idea.

33:36.667 --> 33:39.250
Look, we're really young,
and we're gonna screw up a lot.

33:39.500 --> 33:42.000
You know, we're going to keep
changing our minds and...

33:43.041 --> 33:44.792
And sometimes even our hearts.

33:46.500 --> 33:48.166
And through all of that,
the only real thing

33:48.166 --> 33:50.834
we can offer each other
is forgiveness.

33:52.875 --> 33:54.291
And I couldn't do that.

33:55.291 --> 33:57.000
At least I did it
too late.

33:59.166 --> 34:01.667
Don't let yourself get so angry
that you stop loving

34:01.667 --> 34:05.041
because one day you'll
wake up from that anger,

34:05.708 --> 34:07.917
and the person you love
will be gone.

34:09.875 --> 34:12.125
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

34:13.542 --> 34:15.041
[DOOR OPENS]

34:16.208 --> 34:17.291
[DOOR CLOSES]

34:19.500 --> 34:20.958
I tell you, these fishnets itch.

34:20.958 --> 34:22.375
I can't believe
you're wearing them.

34:22.833 --> 34:23.708
Dad.

34:23.708 --> 34:25.750
Hi, Jack, Jen.

34:27.458 --> 34:29.083
Jack, I'll see you
at home.

34:29.750 --> 34:30.708
Yeah.

34:31.792 --> 34:33.208
Jen's grandmother
called me.

34:33.208 --> 34:35.000
Said I should make
my way down here tonight.

34:35.000 --> 34:37.542
I wasn't sure why
till I saw you up there.

34:40.000 --> 34:41.166
Congratulations.

34:42.792 --> 34:44.583
Thanks... I guess.

34:45.333 --> 34:46.375
[CLEARS THROAT]

34:48.417 --> 34:51.583
Seeing you on that stage
made me realize I was wrong.

34:52.417 --> 34:53.250
How do you mean?

34:53.750 --> 34:56.333
Jack, I honestly thought I was
doing what was best for you.

34:56.333 --> 34:59.834
I thought living under my care
would be too hard,

35:01.417 --> 35:04.041
that there were
too many differences between us.

35:05.083 --> 35:07.083
And when I saw you
in that jersey,

35:08.166 --> 35:10.625
for the first time
in a while,

35:12.250 --> 35:13.792
I saw myself in you.

35:15.583 --> 35:17.417
Dad, it shouldn't take
a football jersey

35:17.417 --> 35:18.625
to make you see that.

35:19.875 --> 35:20.875
You're right.

35:22.917 --> 35:25.166
I would like very much
for you to come home.

35:27.917 --> 35:29.250
Sorry, but no.

35:32.667 --> 35:35.250
Well, I figured that
would be your response,

35:35.959 --> 35:37.291
but I needed to ask.

35:39.875 --> 35:40.834
Thanks.

35:42.625 --> 35:43.750
Good night to you.

35:44.417 --> 35:45.417
Night, Dad.

35:45.750 --> 35:46.667
Dad?

35:48.792 --> 35:49.875
Yeah?

35:51.208 --> 35:52.792
Ask me again sometime.

35:57.250 --> 35:58.834
[DOOR OPENS]

36:03.083 --> 36:05.458
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

36:18.834 --> 36:21.000
I was hoping
you'd find me here.

36:24.417 --> 36:28.083
To be honest, I told myself
a thousand times not to come.

36:30.583 --> 36:32.125
So why did you?

36:33.917 --> 36:35.458
'Cause I owe you
that much.

36:38.458 --> 36:40.208
But I've already told you
how sorry I am.

36:40.208 --> 36:41.667
What else can I say?

36:45.000 --> 36:46.375
There's nothing else
to say.

36:50.834 --> 36:53.166
So you don't think
that you can forgive me?

36:56.542 --> 36:58.542
Whether or not I can
forgive you, Andie,

36:58.542 --> 37:00.875
is not going to be
what keeps us apart.

37:07.250 --> 37:08.500
What you did...

37:09.542 --> 37:10.625
[PACEY SIGHS]

37:11.542 --> 37:16.458
Our relationship
was like this beautiful thing.

37:18.667 --> 37:20.166
And I don't think
you ever realized

37:20.166 --> 37:21.542
how powerful it was.

37:24.375 --> 37:26.750
You changed my life,
Andie.

37:27.583 --> 37:30.458
You were that person for me.

37:31.166 --> 37:33.083
You inspired me
to be a man

37:33.083 --> 37:35.583
that I had only ever
dreamed about being.

37:42.041 --> 37:44.291
When you first started
to get sick...

37:46.959 --> 37:49.250
It dawned on me
that I might not be

37:49.250 --> 37:50.917
that person for you.

37:55.166 --> 37:57.667
I can never go back
to loving you the way I did,

37:57.667 --> 37:59.250
knowing that my love
wasn't strong enough

37:59.250 --> 38:00.750
the first time around.

38:02.166 --> 38:03.125
[SNIFFLES]

38:07.166 --> 38:09.333
I can always
forgive you, Andie...

38:12.000 --> 38:13.458
But I will never forget.

38:19.375 --> 38:20.583
[EXHALES]

38:22.166 --> 38:24.291
But I still love you,
Pacey.

38:26.208 --> 38:27.583
[WATER RIPPLING]

38:28.625 --> 38:29.750
[SNIFFLING]

38:31.125 --> 38:32.917
Good-bye, Andie.

38:39.667 --> 38:40.959
[SNIFFLES]

38:42.125 --> 38:44.708
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

38:45.208 --> 38:46.333
[DOOR CLOSES]

38:47.625 --> 38:50.875
-♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

39:04.000 --> 39:05.542
-Hey.
-Hey.

39:07.917 --> 39:10.208
[SIGHS]
What are you doing here?

39:13.583 --> 39:14.708
I'm not sure.

39:15.959 --> 39:16.959
I guess...

39:17.834 --> 39:19.792
Your house is like
magnetic north.

39:20.625 --> 39:23.375
Certain nights,
it just... it draws me in.

39:25.125 --> 39:26.667
While you were gone
this summer,

39:27.625 --> 39:29.792
there were days I would
just get in my boat

39:29.792 --> 39:32.083
and come riding
past your dock.

39:34.750 --> 39:36.291
For old times' sake, I guess.

39:37.375 --> 39:39.083
-[FROGS CROAKING]
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

39:42.875 --> 39:44.000
[DAWSON SIGHS]

39:46.000 --> 39:47.583
We can't go back, Joey.

39:51.917 --> 39:53.250
I know.

39:55.834 --> 39:57.542
That's the expression,
isn't it?

39:58.917 --> 40:00.500
You can't go home again?

40:02.792 --> 40:04.875
I've realized it
for a while.

40:07.125 --> 40:08.417
Earlier tonight.

40:09.500 --> 40:11.083
I'm sorry you had
to see that.

40:13.917 --> 40:15.250
Don't be.

40:19.125 --> 40:20.583
I think I was meant to.

40:23.083 --> 40:25.875
In some weird way,
it helped me.

40:26.959 --> 40:28.917
I mean, seeing you
on that stage,

40:29.583 --> 40:31.250
something inside
of me clicked,

40:31.542 --> 40:34.875
and for the first time, I...

40:36.750 --> 40:38.375
I felt how wrong
it would be.

40:40.250 --> 40:41.542
I mean, we...

40:42.375 --> 40:46.417
We really do need to move on
and to meet new people

40:46.417 --> 40:48.291
and to have
new relationships.

40:52.834 --> 40:54.708
It's weird
how that happens, isn't it?

40:58.250 --> 40:59.583
You still love the person,

40:59.583 --> 41:01.583
but you stop needing them
like you used to.

41:04.166 --> 41:05.208
Yeah.

41:07.458 --> 41:09.208
It's weird, and...

41:11.625 --> 41:12.959
It's kinda sad.

41:23.291 --> 41:24.208
[SIGHS]

41:30.959 --> 41:32.417
So we're friends...

41:33.333 --> 41:34.834
And then we're a couple...

41:35.291 --> 41:37.041
Then friends again...

41:37.041 --> 41:38.083
Then we're a couple.

41:38.083 --> 41:39.125
So...

41:40.625 --> 41:41.917
[SIGHS]

41:43.542 --> 41:45.041
So what are we now?

41:48.417 --> 41:49.792
We're Dawson and Joey.

41:52.917 --> 41:53.875
[CHUCKLES]

42:05.417 --> 42:08.208
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

42:18.083 --> 42:19.959
[WIND BLOWING]

42:23.667 --> 42:25.125
You think every Joey
has a Dawson,

42:25.125 --> 42:27.333
and every Dawson
has a Joey?

42:27.333 --> 42:28.125
[CHORTLES]

42:30.041 --> 42:31.291
I hope so.

42:33.792 --> 42:34.959
For their sake.

42:38.625 --> 42:41.500
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪
